### TypeORM Integration

Use `@nestjs/typeorm` to integrate TypeORM. Import `TypeOrmModule.forRoot()` in AppModule with database config. Define entities with `@Entity()` decorator. Register entities per-feature with `TypeOrmModule.forFeature([Cat])`. Inject repositories using `@InjectRepository()`.

Repositories provide methods like `find()`, `findOne()`, `save()`, `delete()`. Transaction support is available via `EntityManager` or the `DataSource` object.

```typescript
// cat.entity.ts
@Entity()
export class Cat {
  @PrimaryGeneratedColumn() id: number;
  @Column() name: string;
}

// cats.module.ts
@Module({
  imports: [TypeOrmModule.forFeature([Cat])],
  providers: [CatsService],
})
export class CatsModule {}

// cats.service.ts
@Injectable()
export class CatsService {
  constructor(
    @InjectRepository(Cat)
    private catRepository: Repository<Cat>
  ) {}

  create(name: string) { return this.catRepository.save({ name }); }
  findAll() { return this.catRepository.find(); }
}

// app.module.ts
@Module({
  imports: [
    TypeOrmModule.forRoot({ type: 'postgres', url: process.env.DATABASE_URL, entities: [Cat], synchronize: false }),
    CatsModule,
  ],
})
export class AppModule {}
```

**Common interview trap:** Forgetting to register entities in `TypeOrmModule.forFeature([Cat])` in the feature module causes "Repository<Cat> not found" at startup. Also: never use `synchronize: true` in production — it auto-alters the database schema on every deploy, which can destroy data.

answer.ru:
